  "prompt": "What hand drawn anime is out there?",
  "response": "Hand-drawn anime, also known as traditional animation, has a rich history and continues to be appreciated by audiences around the world. Here are some notable examples of hand-drawn anime:\n\n1. **Studio Ghibli Films**:\n   - *Spirited Away*\n   - *My Neighbor Totoro*\n   - *Princess Mononoke*\n   - *Howl's Moving Castle*\n   - *The Wind Rises*\n\n2. **Classic Anime Series**:\n   - *Astro Boy* (Tetsuwan Atom)\n   - *Mobile Suit Gundam* (and its various iterations)\n   - *Cowboy Bebop*\n   - *Neon Genesis Evangelion*\n   - *Sailor Moon*\n\n3. **Recent Hand-Drawn Titles**:\n   - *Your Name* (Kimi no Na wa)\n   - *A Silent Voice* (Koe no Katachi)\n   - *Weathering With You* (Tenki no Ko)\n   - *Promare* (stylized but hand-drawn elements)\n\n4. **Short Films and OVAs**:\n   - *The Garden of Words* (Kotonoha no Niwa)\n   - *Little Witch Academia*\n   - *Miss Hokusai*\n   - *In This Corner of the World* (Kono Sekai no Katasumi ni)\n\n5. **Hand-Drawn Series**:\n   - *Attack on Titan* (originally hand-drawn before incorporating some digital techniques)\n   - *One Piece* (though it utilizes digital techniques, it maintains a traditional style)\n   - *Mob Psycho 100*\n\n6. **Artistic and Experimental Works**:\n   - *Mind Game*\n   - *The Night is Short, Walk on Girl* (Yoake no Tori, Kokoro no Oka)\n\nWhile many modern anime utilize digital techniques, they often still retain a hand-drawn aesthetic or incorporate hand-drawn elements, so the distinction can sometimes blur. The love for traditional animation persists, keeping hand-drawn artistry alive in various forms.",
